.TH "snd_lookup_minor_data" 9 "snd_lookup_minor_data" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_lookup_minor_data \- get user data of a registered device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" snd_lookup_minor_data
.BI "(unsigned int minor "  ","
.BI "int type "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "minor" 12
the minor number
.IP "type" 12
device type (SNDRV_DEVICE_TYPE_XXX)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Checks that a minor device with the specified type is registered, and returns
its user data pointer.

This function increments the reference counter of the card instance
if an associated instance with the given minor number and type is found.
The caller must call \fBsnd_card_unref\fP appropriately later.
.SH "RETURN"
The user data pointer if the specified device is found. NULL
otherwise.
